# Dev-only paths kept in this repo for the maintainer's own history/tooling but
# excluded from the distributed archive. GitHub's tarball download and `git archive`
# honor export-ignore, so these never ship to a consuming repo.
#
# Without this, `do-work update` (curl | tar of the main-branch tarball) would extract
# the maintainer's own queue/archive and sample reports into a consumer's skill
# directory. They land in the wrong place (nested under the skill dir, not the
# consumer's project root) so they don't corrupt anything, but they're shipped clutter.
# The install/update tar command also passes --exclude for do-work/ai-reports/_dev plus
# .vscode/decisions as a belt-and-suspenders fallback for tarballs built before this file
# existed. The dev dotfiles (.gitignore/.gitattributes) are export-ignore-only — excluding
# them via tar is awkward and a stale vendored copy leaks nothing (export-ignore is inert
# once the skill is a subdirectory of a consumer's repo).
#
# decisions/ holds the maintainer's own ADRs about this skill — design history, never
# loaded at runtime by any action — so consumers don't need it. The dev dotfiles
# (.gitignore/.gitattributes) are repo-maintenance plumbing that's meaningless once the
# skill is a subdirectory of someone else's repo. All are excluded for a clean install.
/do-work         export-ignore
/CHANGELOG-archive.md export-ignore
/ai-reports      export-ignore
/.vscode         export-ignore
/_dev            export-ignore
/decisions       export-ignore
/.gitignore      export-ignore
/.gitattributes  export-ignore
